  "batteries": {
    "section_id": "batteries",
    "version": "v4.21",
    "provenance_map": [
      {
        "id": "S1",
        "sentence": "On Supernova, the house bank is three house batteries (Mastervolt MLI Ultra 24/6000), about 18 kWh together.",
        "sources": [
          "graph.device:mli_ultra_1",
          "graph.device:mli_ultra_2",
          "graph.device:mli_ultra_3",
          "vessel.display_name",
          "profile.mli_ultra.device.model",
          "equipment.mli_ultra.quantity",
          "equipment.mli_ultra.model"
        ],
        "kind": "composed_inference",
        "block": "capability_summary",
        "composed_inference": true,
        "contributing_facts": [
          "equipment.mli_ultra.model=MLI Ultra 24/6000",
          "equipment.mli_ultra.quantity=3",
          "profile.mli_ultra.device.model",
          "derived:6000_Wh_token_per_unit_from_model",
          "derived:bank_kWh≈3×6",
          "vessel.display_name"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "S2",
        "sentence": "Solar arrays feed the bank through Victron MPPT chargers. Two inverter-chargers (Mastervolt Mass Combi Pro) convert between shore or generator AC and the house bank, and supply AC from the bank when no shore or generator power is available. The generator (Fischer Panda 8000i) supplies on-board AC when shore power is unavailable. Two alternator regulators (Mastervolt Alpha Pro III) manage twin 24 V / 110 A engine-driven alternators when the engines are running. Array layout, VictronConnect checks, and boom-shade cautions are in the Solar notes that accompany this chapter.",
        "sources": [
          "graph.device:victron_mppt",
          "graph.device:victron_mppt_150_60",
          "leaf:solar",
          "graph.device:mass_combi_pro_1",
          "graph.device:mass_combi_pro_2",
          "profile.mass_combi_pro.operator_actions",
          "graph.device:fischer_panda_8000i",
          "profile.fischer_panda_8000i.device",
          "profile.fischer_panda_8000i.operator_actions",
          "equipment.alpha_pro.provenance_split.attested",
          "graph.device:alpha_pro_iii_port",
          "graph.device:alpha_pro_iii_stbd",
          "profile.alpha_pro_iii.operator_actions"
        ],
        "kind": "sourced",
        "block": "how_it_works",
        "provenance_metadata": [
          "path_device:masterbus_bridge_interface"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "S3",
        "sentence": "Watch house-bank state of charge and any alarms as part of daily energy checks; bank and meter readings on the CZone touchscreen, including the Inverter Charger page for the inverter-chargers, can be found in the Controls and Monitoring section of this guide.",
        "sources": [
          "graph.device:mli_ultra_1",
          "graph.device:mli_ultra_2",
          "graph.device:mli_ultra_3",
          "profile.mli_ultra.safety_role",
          "section_inputs.excluded:czone_touch_7",
          "xref.controls",
          "profile.czone_2_0.ui_pages[Inverter Charger]"
        ],
        "kind": "sourced",
        "block": "monitoring",
        "links": [
          {
            "target_kind": "system",
            "target_id": "controls",
            "label": "Controls and Monitoring section of this guide",
            "data_guide_link": "system:controls"
          }
        ],
        "provenance_metadata": [
          "path_device:masterbus_bridge_interface"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "S4",
        "sentence": "At anchor in good sun, treat solar as the main charge path across both arrays; when the engines are running, those alternators add engine-driven charging.",
        "sources": [
          "vessel_fact:solar_davit_array_observation",
          "vessel_fact:solar_coachroof_array_observation",
          "graph.device:victron_mppt",
          "graph.device:victron_mppt_150_60",
          "graph.device:alpha_pro_iii_port",
          "graph.device:alpha_pro_iii_stbd",
          "equipment.alpha_pro.provenance_split.attested"
        ],
        "kind": "composed_inference",
        "block": "monitoring",
        "composed_inference": true,
        "contributing_facts": [
          "solar_davit_array_observation",
          "solar_coachroof_array_observation",
          "derived:at_anchor_solar_primary_vs_engines_running_alternators",
          "equipment.alpha_pro_iii_port.provenance_split.attested",
          "equipment.alpha_pro_iii_stbd.provenance_split.attested",
          "equipment.alpha quantity=2"
        ],
        "provenance_metadata": [
          "path_device:masterbus_bridge_interface"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "S5",
        "sentence": "When shore or mains AC input is limited, to avoid tripping the external AC circuit breaker, set the AC input current limit from the Combi front panel on the inverter-charger, or the CZone Inverter Charger page on the touchscreen.",
        "sources": [
          "profile.mass_combi_pro.operator_actions",
          "profile.mass_combi_pro.operator_actions.occasion",
          "profile.mass_combi_pro.control_surfaces[0]",
          "profile.mass_combi_pro.data_roles.controllable_from_network",
          "profile.czone_2_0.ui_pages[Inverter Charger]",
          "graph.device:mass_combi_pro_1",
          "graph.device:mass_combi_pro_2"
        ],
        "kind": "sourced",
        "block": "adjusting",
        "provenance_metadata": [
          "path_device:masterbus_bridge_interface"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "S6",
        "sentence": "Start and stop the generator from its Panda iControl2 panel, and give it a visual check before starting.",
        "sources": [
          "graph.device:fischer_panda_8000i",
          "profile.fischer_panda_8000i.control_surfaces[0]",
          "profile.fischer_panda_8000i.operator_actions"
        ],
        "kind": "sourced",
        "block": "adjusting",
        "provenance_metadata": [
          "path_device:masterbus_bridge_interface"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "S7",
        "sentence": "The house batteries protect themselves through their BMS — a protective disconnect is the system doing its job, uncommon in normal use, and recoverable with a reset. After a protective disconnect, reset the BMS on the affected house battery before restoring loads.",
        "sources": [
          "graph.device:mli_ultra_1",
          "graph.device:mli_ultra_2",
          "graph.device:mli_ultra_3",
          "profile.mli_ultra.safety_role.is_protective_device",
          "profile.mli_ultra.safety_role.has_emergency_procedure",
          "profile.mli_ultra.operator_actions",
          "profile.mli_ultra.evidence:BMS_disconnect_reset"
        ],
        "kind": "composed_inference",
        "block": "troubleshooting",
        "composed_inference": true,
        "contributing_facts": [
          "profile.mli_ultra.safety_role.is_protective_device=true",
          "profile.mli_ultra.safety_role.has_emergency_procedure=true",
          "profile.mli_ultra.safety_role.has_manual_override=true",
